            "text": "Low - and middle - income countries ,",
            "relation": "BACKGROUND"
        },
        {
            "id": 2,
            "parent": 1,
            "text": "where emerging diseases often make their debut ,",
            "relation": "ELABORATION"
        },
        {
            "id": 3,
            "parent": 1,
            "text": "are also likely to bear the harshest consequences of a potential influenza pandemic . <S>",
            "relation": "SAME-UNIT"
        },
        {
            "id": 4,
            "parent": 1,
            "text": "Yet public health systems in developing countries are underfunded , understaffed , and in many cases struggling to deal with the existing burden of disease . <S>",
            "relation": "COMPARISON"
        },
        {
            "id": 5,
            "parent": 4,
            "text": "As a result , developed countries are beginning to expand assistance for emergency preparedness to the developing world . <S>",
            "relation": "CAUSE-RESULT"
        },
        {
            "id": 6,
            "parent": 7,
            "text": "Given developing countries ' weak infrastructure and many competing public health priorities ,",
            "relation": "CONDITION"
        },
        {
            "id": 7,
            "parent": 5,
            "text": "it is not clear how to best direct these resources . <S>",
            "relation": "COMPARISON"
        },
        {
            "id": 8,
            "parent": 9,
            "text": "Evidence from the U.S. and other developed countries suggests",
            "relation": "ATTRIBUTION"
        },
        {
            "id": 9,
            "parent": 7,
            "text": "that some investments in bioterror and pandemic emergency preparedness ,",
            "relation": "ELABORATION"
        },
        {
            "id": 10,
            "parent": 9,
            "text": "although initially implemented as vertical programs ,",
            "relation": "COMPARISON"
        },
        {
            "id": 11,
            "parent": 9,
            "text": "have the potential to strengthen the general public health infrastructure . <S>",
            "relation": "SAME-UNIT"
        },
        {
            "id": 12,
            "parent": 0,
            "text": "This experience may hold some lessons for",
            "relation": "ROOT"
        },
        {
            "id": 13,
            "parent": 12,
            "text": "how global funds for emergency preparedness could be invested in developing countries",
            "relation": "ELABORATION"
        },
        {
            "id": 14,
            "parent": 12,
            "text": "to support struggling public health systems",
            "relation": "ENABLEMENT"
        },
        {
            "id": 15,
            "parent": 14,
            "text": "in responding to current health priorities as well as potential future public health threats . <S>",
            "relation": "ELABORATION"
        },
